

Draft email acknowledgement to submitter following VO registration:

&quot;Hello and Welcome to the Open Science Grid! Thank you for  registering the [VO_Name] Virtual Organization. By completing the VO  Registration form you have started the approval process to have your  VO added to the OSG. A detailed flowchart of the approval process can  be found at http://osg.ivdgl.org/twiki/bin/view/Operations/StandardOperatingProcedures. This process should take approximately 7 business  days to complete.

Your VO will be presented for approval to the OSG Council on the first Thursday after it is submitted and then sent to the next Operations Workgroup for discussion on the next Monday. If you would  like to attend the Operations Workgroup meeting to represent your VO and inform the community of your participation and goal in joining  the OSG you can find the details at http://osg.ivdgl.org/twiki/bin/view/Operations/ProductionMeetingMinutes.

There are several mailing lists associated with the OSG, as a new VO  you may want to subscribe to the following mailing lists:

osg@opensciencegrid.org  -- For general OSG announcements

osg-general@opensciencegrid.org  -- For general technical discussion  and open community support

osg-operations@opensciencegrid.org  -- Discussion of operations activities and issues

osg-ops-status@opensciencegrid.org  -- Daily OSG Status Reports

vo-admins@opensciencegrid.org  -- Discussion of OSG VO and GUMS Administration

Details for subscribing to these lists and a list of other OSG  mailing lists you may be interested in subscribing to can be found at  http://www.opensciencegrid.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=75&amp;Itemid=88.

Please contact the Grid Operations Center (GOC) at  goc@opensciencegrid.org if you have any questions.

Thank you for your interest in the OSG, and we look forward to your  participation in the OSG Consortium!

OSG Operations Workgroup&quot;


